o	Platforms I used: 
o	For this task I used two platforms - HackerRank for coding practice and Google Forms for building a collaborative quiz tool.

	HackerRank:
o	On HackerRank I completed the Solve Me First challenge, which is a beginner-level Python problem. It sounds simple and it is ,but actually submitting code on a judge platform for the first time feels different from just writing it in a notebook. You realise quickly that the code either works or it doesn't, and there's no partial credit for "almost right."

	Google form:
o	The more interesting part was building the Digital Literacy Quiz on Google Forms. I put together five questions covering phishing, UPI safety, 2FA, and cybercrime reporting. Linking it to a Google Sheet so responses populate automatically was something I hadn't properly explored before it's genuinely useful for collecting data without any manual work.

	Conclusion:
o	Both tools are ones I'll keep using. HackerRank for staying sharp with problem-solving, and Google Forms any time I need to gather feedback or run a quick survey for a college projec
